      "id": 355114,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Photolysis of the <i>cis</i>-cyclobutene isomer in Problem 30-37 yields <i>cis</i>-cyclododecaen-7-yne, but photolysis of the trans isomer yields <i>trans</i>-cyclododecaen-7-yne. Explain these results, and identify the type and stereochemistry of the pericyclic reaction.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZzhhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--65323240bcf73c1c6939921eead0e2dbf9cb5f13/OChem_30_EC_023.jpg\" alt=\"Cis cyclobutene isomer undergoes a photochemical reaction to give cis-cyclododecaen-7-yne. The trans-isomer undergoes a photochemical reaction to give trans-cyclododecaen-7-yne. A double bond is between C 1 and C 2.\">",
